<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="654" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1359,2287,3266]" pageId="35" pageNumber="654">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[152,287,2879,2912]" pageId="35" pageNumber="654">Breeding.</emphasis>
Pregnant females have been recorded in September in north-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[153,302,2919,2952]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="35" pageNumber="654">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
and in March in western 
<collectingCountry box="[681,794,2919,2952]" name="Uganda" pageId="35" pageNumber="654">Uganda</collectingCountry>
. Where noted, pregnant females had a single embryo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="654" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1359,2287,3266]" pageId="35" pageNumber="654">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,389,2997,3030]" pageId="35" pageNumber="654">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[404,497,2997,3030]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="35" pageNumber="654">Congo</collectingCountry>
Free-tailed Bats are nocturnal and, based on the finding of the type series, roost in hollow trees.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="654" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1359,2287,3266]" pageId="35" pageNumber="654">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[152,873,3076,3109]" pageId="35" pageNumber="654">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
Based on the type series, 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1356,3076,3109]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="35" pageNumber="654">Congo</collectingCountry>
Free-tailed Bats roost communally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
